# Code Structure
- Organize by feature, not technical layer
- Keep all feature code (implementation, tests, errors, interfaces) in single package
- Use internal/ for private implementations
- Keep functions small and focused

# Development Process
- Always write table-driven tests first before implementation
- Achieve 100% test coverage for core components
- Use explicit error types and proper error wrapping
- Use interfaces for dependencies and testing
- Use context.Context in public APIs

# Go Best Practices
- No global variables or state
- Use dependency injection
- Follow Go naming conventions (CamelCase exported, camelCase private)
- Use structured logging
- Handle all errors explicitly, no bare returns
- Document all exported items with GoDoc

# Quality Requirements
- Run tests with -race and -cover flags
- Verify test failures before implementation
- Use golangci-lint and go vet
- Prevent race conditions
- Keep dependencies minimal and explicit
